name: Boar's Head recall
summary: Boar's Head has initiated a major recall, affecting over 200,000 pounds of its deli meats. This recall is a response to a Listeria outbreak that has impacted multiple states and resulted in several hospitalizations and one fatality. The affected products include various sliced meats and liverwurst, and consumers are urged to discard any products with the specified lot numbers. Major retailers like Big Y have temporarily closed their deli counters due to the recall. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) advises consumers to avoid consuming the recalled meats and seek medical attention if they experience symptoms of Listeria infection, which include fever, muscle aches, and gastrointestinal issues. Individuals with weakened immune systems are particularly vulnerable and should take extra precautions.
